[[2010年英國大選|2010年英國大選的競選期]]間，里斯-莫格被《[[星期日泰晤士報|星期日泰晤士報]]》編輯{{le|卡米拉·朗|Camilla Long}}在候選人的人物簡介上評為「[[戴维·卡梅伦|戴维·卡梅伦]]最糟的噩夢」<ref name="long">{{Cite news |last=Long |first=Camilla |date=2010-04-11 |title=Maybe he's canvassing in the King of Spain's private loo |work=The Sunday Times |url=http://www.thesundaytimes.co.uk/sto/news/Election/article258682.ece |access-date=2015-03-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402114148/http://www.thesundaytimes.co.uk/sto/news/Election/article258682.ece |archive-date=2015-04-02}}</ref>。那場選舉中，他成為了保守黨在新選區[[東北薩默塞特_(英國國會選區)|東北薩默塞特]]的[[國會議員_(英國)|國會議員]]參選人，並最後成功當選，領先第二名4,914票<ref name="2010Res">{{Cite news |date=2010-05-07 |title=Election 2010 – Somerset North East |work=BBC News |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/shared/election2010/results/constituency/d20.stm}}</ref>。他的妹妹新聞記者{{le|安农齐亚塔·里斯-莫格|Annunziata Rees-Mogg|-{安農齊亞塔·里斯-莫格}-}}同時在鄰近的[[薩默頓和弗羅姆_(英國國會選區)|薩默頓和弗羅姆選區]]參選，但以1,817票之差未能勝出<ref name="Adams2" /><ref>{{Cite news |title=Somerton & Frome |work=BBC News |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/shared/election2010/results/constituency/e07.stm |access-date=2013-10-03}}</ref>。《[[衛報|衛報]]》撰稿人{{le|伊恩·傑克|Ian Jack}}認為挑選兩個富裕階層的人出選，破壞了保守黨所提倡建立包容社會的訊息，暗示這樣的參選人應被排除在外。<ref name="Jack" />

==== 卡麥隆內閣（2010－16年） ====
2010年，{{le|保守黨之家|ConservativeHome}}網誌列里斯-莫格其中一個最桀驁不馴的國會議員<ref name="conhome">{{Cite web |last=Isaby, Jonathan |date=2010-12-15 |title=Philip Hollobone continues to top the league table of backbench rebels |url=http://conservativehome.blogs.com/parliament/2010/12/the-latest-league-table-of-tory-backbench-rebellion.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130307230411/http://conservativehome.blogs.com/parliament/2010/12/the-latest-league-table-of-tory-backbench-rebellion.html |archive-date=2013-03-07 |publisher=ConservativeHome}}</ref>。他曾違反[[黨鞭|黨鞭]]，反對《[[英國定期國會法|英國定期國會草案]]》、2011年10月歐盟公投動議以及《{{le|2012年上議院改革草案|House of Lords Reform Bill 2012}}》<ref name="publicwhip">{{Cite web |title=Voting Record — Jacob Rees-Mogg MP, North East Somerset (24926) |url=http://www.publicwhip.org.uk/mp.php?mpn=Jacob_Rees-Mogg&mpc=North_East_Somerset&house=commons |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120326083305/http://www.publicwhip.org.uk/mp.php?mpn=Jacob_Rees-Mogg&mpc=North_East_Somerset&house=commons |archive-date=2012-03-26 |access-date=2012-07-15 |website=The Public Whip |publisher=Bairwell}}</ref>。

[[英国下议院|下議院]]內，里斯-莫格因其幽默的演說和「[[冗長辯論|拉布]]」能力而為人所知曉<ref>{{Cite news |last=Wright |first=Oliver |date=2013-01-06 |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg: 'I'm suspicious of politicians who try to be men of the people' |work=[[The_Independent|The Independent]] |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/jacob-rees-mogg-im-suspicious-of-politicians-who-try-to-be-men-of-the-people-8440276.html |access-date=2017-08-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170806180546/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/jacob-rees-mogg-im-suspicious-of-politicians-who-try-to-be-men-of-the-people-8440276.html |archive-date=2017-08-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |date=2017-07-06 |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg, the Internet's favourite MP |url=http://www.theweek.co.uk/86423/jacob-rees-mogg-the-internets-favourite-mp |magazine=[[The_Week|The Week]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170807235658/http://www.theweek.co.uk/86423/jacob-rees-mogg-the-internets-favourite-mp |archive-date=2017-08-07 |access-date=2017-08-07}}</ref><ref name="cult">{{Cite news |date=2011-07-01 |title=The cult of Jacob Rees-Mogg |work=[[Total_Politics|Total Politics]] |url=http://www.totalpolitics.com/articles/162077/the-cult-of-jacob-reesmogg.thtml |access-date=2012-07-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110903050256/http://www.totalpolitics.com/articles/162077/the-cult-of-jacob-reesmogg.thtml |archive-date=2011-09-03}}</ref>。他在《{{le|2010年日光節約草案|Daylight Saving Bill 2010|2010-12年日光節約草案}}》和《2010-12年可持續家禽草案》上「拉布」，成功阻止兩項法案在國會通過。他在後者法案的發言時，背誦了詩詞、談及了森麻實郡所出產的蛋有多優秀、講述在虛構故事中連續於{{le|史樂郡秀|Shropshire County Show}}贏了三次的{{le|布蘭德女皇|Empress of Blandings}}、又提述到污水處理系統、還有[[阿金库尔战役|阿金库尔战役]]<ref name="cult" /><ref>{{Cite web |date=2010-11-12 |title=Sustainable Livestock Bill |url=https://www.theyworkforyou.com/debates/?id=2010-11-12a.549.0&s=speaker%3A24926#g605.19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131002205207/http://www.theyworkforyou.com/debates/?id=2010-11-12a.549.0&s=speaker%3A24926#g605.19 |archive-date=2013-10-02 |access-date=2012-07-15 |website=They Work for You |publisher=[[mySociety|mySociety]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2012-11-15 |title=Friday filibusters and mug poetry |url=http://labourlist.org/2010/11/friday-filibusters-and-mug-poetry/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130218145338/http://labourlist.org/2010/11/friday-filibusters-and-mug-poetry/ |archive-date=2013-02-18 |access-date=2012-07-14 |publisher=LabourList}}</ref><ref>{{cite Hansard |title=Sustainable Livestock Bill |url=https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201011/cmhansrd/cm101112/debtext/101112-0002.htm |house=[[House_of_Commons_of_the_United_Kingdom|House of Commons of the United Kingdom]] |date=2010-11-12 |column=605 |speaker=Jacob Rees-Mogg |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140407074835/http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201011/cmhansrd/cm101112/debtext/101112-0002.htm |archivedate=2014-04-07}}</ref>。他亦同時就前者法案提出修正案，試圖讓森麻實郡擁有比倫敦慢15分鐘的獨立[[时区|时区]]<ref>{{Cite news |date=2012-01-18 |title=Tory MP calls for Somerset to have its own time zone |work=BBC News |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-16611058 |access-date=2012-07-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120120193443/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-16611058 |archive-date=2012-01-20}}</ref>。

在2011年12月有關《倫敦地方政府草案》的一項辯論中，他認為有權即場罰款的地區政府官員應該要戴上[[圓頂硬禮帽|圓頂硬禮帽]]<ref>{{Cite web |date=2011-11-07 |title=Clause 3 – Powers exercisable by police civilians and accredited persons |url=https://www.theyworkforyou.com/debates/?id=2011-12-07a.326.2#g329.0 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131002205157/http://www.theyworkforyou.com/debates/?id=2011-12-07a.326.2#g329.0 |archive-date=2013-10-02 |access-date=2012-07-15 |website=They Work for You |publisher=mySociety}}</ref>。2012年2月的一場國會辯論上，他使用了「[[wikt:floccinaucinihilipilification|floccinaucinihilipilification]]」一詞（意指被視為無用的習慣），打破了下議院發言中最長單字的紀錄<ref>{{Cite web |title=I have great sympathy with what the...: 21 Feb 2012: House of Commons debates |url=https://www.theyworkforyou.com/debates/?id=2012-02-21b.787.1 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170731025511/https://www.theyworkforyou.com/debates/?id=2012-02-21b.787.1 |archive-date=2017-07-31 |access-date=2019-05-30 |website=TheyWorkForYou}}</ref>。

