2013年5月，他在{{le|傳統英國集團|Traditional Britain Group}}的年度晚宴上致辭，那是一個呼籲驅逐所有非白人的英國國民出境的[[極右派|極右翼]]團體。[[反法西斯主義|反法西斯主義]]團體《{{le|探照燈 (雜誌)|Searchlight (magazine)|探照燈}}》在他到席前已經通知他該團體的性質，但他仍然決定出席。在晚宴完結後，他表示知道該團體的立場，但「從來不是他們的成員或支持者」<ref>{{Cite news |last=Nigel Morris |date=2013-08-08 |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg's after-dinner speech to group calling on Doreen Lawrence to 'go home' |work=The Telegraph |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/jacob-rees-mogg-s-after-dinner-speech-to-group-calling-on-doreen-lawrence-to-go-home-8752995.html |access-date=2018-02-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Holehouse |first=Matthew |date=2013-08-08 |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg's shock at dinner with group that want to repatriate black Britons |work=The Daily Telegraph |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/politics/10230962/Jacob-Rees-Moggs-shock-at-dinner-with-group-that-want-to-repatriate-black-Britons.html |access-date=2013-08-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130811152805/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/politics/10230962/Jacob-Rees-Moggs-shock-at-dinner-with-group-that-want-to-repatriate-black-Britons.html |archive-date=2013-08-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Morris |first=Nigel |date=2013-08-08 |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg's after-dinner speech to group calling on Doreen Lawrence to 'go home' |work=[[The_Independent|The Independent]] |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/jacob-reesmoggs-afterdinner-speech-to-group-calling-on-doreen-lawrence-to-go-home-8752995.html |access-date=2015-02-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150226035638/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/jacob-reesmoggs-afterdinner-speech-to-group-calling-on-doreen-lawrence-to-go-home-8752995.html |archive-date=2015-02-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Mason |first=Rowena |date=2013-08-08 |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg 'shocked' by right-wing group's attack on Lawrence |work=The Guardian |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2013/aug/08/rees-mogg-rightwing-lawrence-attack |access-date=2015-02-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150226024711/http://www.theguardian.com/politics/2013/aug/08/rees-mogg-rightwing-lawrence-attack |archive-date=2015-02-26}}</ref>。

2014年1月，里斯-莫格形容25萬英鎊用作國會議員的肖像照為瑣碎的，「我完全贊成節省金錢，任何時候也處處節省，但這不過是九牛一毛」<ref>{{Cite news |last=Edgar |first=James |date=2014-01-14 |title=MP dismisses £250,000 taxpayer bill for politicians' portraits as 'chicken feed' |work=The Telegraph |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/politics/10571595/MP-dismisses-250000-taxpayer-bill-for-politicianss-portraits-as-chicken-feed.html |access-date=2016-03-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160330163936/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/politics/10571595/MP-dismisses-250000-taxpayer-bill-for-politicianss-portraits-as-chicken-feed.html |archive-date=2016-03-30}}</ref>。同年12月，有市民到{{le|獨立國會標準局|Independent Parliamentary Standards Authority}}舉報里斯-莫格，因為他就有關煙草、採礦、石油及天然氣發言時，沒有預先口頭申報利益，表明他是「森麻實資本管理有限公司」的合夥創辦人兼董事，該公司管理在這些行業數以百萬英鎊計的投資<ref>{{Cite news |last=Merrick |first=Jane |date=2014-12-14 |title=Leading Tory backbench MP Jacob Rees-Mogg 'failed to declare interests' |work=The Independent |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/tory-backbench-mp-jacob-reesmogg-failed-to-declare-interests-9923362.html |access-date=2014-02-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141214025859/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/tory-backbench-mp-jacob-reesmogg-failed-to-declare-interests-9923362.html |archive-date=2014-12-14}}</ref>。時任{{le|國會標準事務專員|Parliamentary Commissioner for Standards}}裁定沒有違規，故而不用開展調查程序<ref>{{Cite news |date=2015-01-05 |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg will face no investigation over declaration of interests |work=The Bristol Post |url=http://www.bristolpost.co.uk/Jacob-Rees-Mogg-face-investigation-declaration/story-25808158-detail/story.html |access-date=2015-03-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150114160226/http://www.bristolpost.co.uk/Jacob-Rees-Mogg-face-investigation-declaration/story-25808158-detail/story.html |archive-date=2015-01-14}}</ref>。根據《[[每日电讯报|每日电讯报]]》，里斯-莫格在2014年國會外的工作時數共有476小時，或每週9小時。<ref>{{Cite news |last1=Telford |first1=Lyndsey |last2=Heighton |first2=Luke |date=2015-02-22 |title=The MPs who topped up their salaries with £1,600-an-hour second jobs |work=The Daily Telegraph |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/investigations/11428075/The-MPs-who-topped-up-their-salaries-with-1600-an-hour-second-jobs.html |access-date=2015-02-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150223213505/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/investigations/11428075/The-MPs-who-topped-up-their-salaries-with-1600-an-hour-second-jobs.html |archive-date=2015-02-23}}</ref>

==== -{zh-hans:梅; zh-hant:梅伊; zh-hk:文翠珊;}-內閣（2016－19年） ====
[[File:Jacob_Rees-Mogg_entertains_guests_at_yesterday's_gala_dinner_of_The_Thorney_Island_Society_(29917777736).jpg|thumb]]

[[戴维·卡梅伦|戴维·卡梅伦]]因[[英國去留歐盟公投|脫歐公投結果]]而辭任[[保守黨黨魁_(英國)|保守黨黨魁]]，觸發[[2016年英國保守黨黨魁選舉|黨魁選舉]]。里斯-莫格打算支持原計劃參選的[[鲍里斯·约翰逊|鲍里斯·约翰逊]]，但其黨魁競選經理[[高文浩|高文浩]]在他計劃宣布參選的早上突然宣布自己參選，約翰遜因而決定不再角逐黨魁。里斯-莫格轉為支持[[利雅華|利雅華]]，但她其後退選，令[[文翠珊|文翠珊]]自動當選黨魁、及後成為首相<ref>{{Cite news |last1=Sparrow |first1=Andrew |last2=Siddique |first2=Haroon |last3=Khomami |first3=Nadia |last4=Johnston |first4=Chris |date=2016-06-30 |title=Boris Johnson says he is out of Tory party leadership race after Gove challenge – as it happened |work=The Guardian |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/live/2016/jun/30/brexit-live-theresa-may-and-boris-johnson-set-to-announce-leadership-bids |access-date=2017-10-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171001165201/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/live/2016/jun/30/brexit-live-theresa-may-and-boris-johnson-set-to-announce-leadership-bids |archive-date=2017-10-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Crace |first=John |date=2016-10-14 |title=Trump loses support of Jacob Rees-Mogg ... but he may be secretly relieved |work=The Guardian |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/oct/14/donald-trump-loses-support-of-mp-but-he-may-be-secretly-relieved |access-date=2017-10-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171001213039/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/oct/14/donald-trump-loses-support-of-mp-but-he-may-be-secretly-relieved |archive-date=2017-10-01}}</ref>。

[[File:Official_portrait_of_Mr_Jacob_Rees-Mogg_crop_2.jpg|thumb]]
2017年，他贊成保守黨與[[民主统一党_(北爱尔兰)|民主統一黨]]的[[信任供给|信任供给]]{{le|保守黨-民主統一黨協議|Conservative-DUP agreement|協議}}<ref>{{Cite news |date=2017-06-26 |title=DUP deal will make the Tories the nasty party again, says Lord Patten |work=[[The_Daily_Telegraph|The Daily Telegraph]] |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/06/26/dup-deal-will-make-tories-nasty-party-says-lord-patten/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170910065724/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/06/26/dup-deal-will-make-tories-nasty-party-says-lord-patten/ |archive-date=2017-09-10}}</ref>，更出席了一個民主統一黨的籌款活動，惹來{{le|北愛爾蘭保守黨|Northern Ireland Conservatives}}的不滿和批評。<ref>{{Cite news |date=2019-02-01 |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg defends attendance at DUP fundraiser hosted by Ian Paisley |work=[[Belfast_Telegraph|Belfast Telegraph]] |url=https://m.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/news/northern-ireland/jacob-reesmogg-defends-attendance-at-dup-fundraiser-hosted-by-ian-paisley-37772806.html}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=2019-02-01 |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg's attendance at DUP fundraiser queried by his party |work=[[Irish_Times|Irish Times]] |url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/politics/jacob-rees-mogg-s-attendance-at-dup-fundraiser-queried-by-his-party-1.3779045}}</ref>

里斯-莫格曾被許多視為角逐黨魁的潛在參選人，而他本人據報也在2017年考慮過<ref>{{Cite news |date=2017-08-09 |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg is the second most popular choice to be next Tory leader among party members |work=[[Business_Insider|Business Insider]] |url=http://uk.businessinsider.com/jacob-rees-mogg-next-tory-leader-2017-8?r=US&IR=T |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170813184626/http://uk.businessinsider.com/jacob-rees-mogg-next-tory-leader-2017-8?r=US&IR=T |archive-date=2017-08-13}}</ref><ref name="auto">{{Cite news |date=2017-07-18 |title='The times change, and we change with them': Jacob Rees-Mogg gets Twitter |work=[[The_Daily_Telegraph|The Daily Telegraph]] |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/07/18/times-change-change-jacob-rees-mogg-gets-twitter/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170719071402/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/07/18/times-change-change-jacob-rees-mogg-gets-twitter/ |archive-date=2017-07-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=2017-08-13 |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg mulls Tory leadership bid |work=The Times |url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/tory-rees-mogg-toys-with-leadership-pdgt9qfvr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=2017-08-13 |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg 'sounds out friends' about his leadership ambitions |work=The Daily Telegraph |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/08/13/jacob-rees-mogg-sounds-tory-leadership-ambitions/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170813160234/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/08/13/jacob-rees-mogg-sounds-tory-leadership-ambitions/ |archive-date=2017-08-13}}</ref>。然而於2017年8月13日，他說這些臆測僅是傳媒在「無聊季節」時的報導<ref>{{Cite news |last=Sparrow |first=Andrew |date=2017-08-13 |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg brushes off leadership talk – but does not rule out bid |work=Guardian |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/aug/13/jacob-rees-mogg-brushes-off-conservative-leadership-talk-but-does-not-rule-out-bid |access-date=2017-08-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170815150028/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/aug/13/jacob-rees-mogg-brushes-off-conservative-leadership-talk-but-does-not-rule-out-bid |archive-date=2017-08-15}}</ref>。保守黨國會議員{{le|海蒂·艾琳|Heidi Allen}}和[[安娜·苏布里|安娜·苏布里]]表明，一旦里斯-莫格成為黨魁，她們將脫離保守黨，前內閣大臣[[簡意寧|簡意寧]]亦說可能會跟隨<ref>{{Cite news |date=2017-08-14 |title=Tory MP: I'll Quit Party If Rees-Mogg Is Made Leader |work=HuffPost UK |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/tory-mp-will-quit-party-if-jacob-rees-mogg-is-made-leader_uk_5990cd7fe4b08a24727553bf?ncid=engmodushpmg00000003 |access-date=2017-09-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170829115416/http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/tory-mp-will-quit-party-if-jacob-rees-mogg-is-made-leader_uk_5990cd7fe4b08a24727553bf?ncid=engmodushpmg00000003 |archive-date=2017-08-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=2017-02-06 |title=Tory MP Anna Soubry threatens to quit party if Brexiteers like Jacob Rees-Mogg and Boris Johnson take over |work=[[Evening_Standard|Evening Standard]] |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/politics/tory-mp-anna-soubry-threatens-to-quit-party-if-brexiteers-like-jacob-reesmogg-and-boris-johnson-take-a3758786.html}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Coates, Sam |date=2018-02-06 |title=Greening hints at party exit if Rees-Mogg becomes PM |url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/greening-hints-at-party-exit-if-rees-mogg-becomes-pm-9hr7sjjs7 |via=www.thetimes.co.uk}}</ref>。不過，有其他保守黨籍的國會議員，如[[傑西·諾曼|傑西·諾曼]]還有[[丹尼爾·考辛斯基|丹尼爾·考辛斯基]]表示，如果里斯-莫格競逐黨魁，他們將會支持<ref>{{Cite news |date=2017-08-23 |title=Hereford and South Herefordshire MP backs Jacob Rees-Mogg |work=Ross Gazette |url=http://www.rossgazette.com/article.cfm?id=109758&headline=Hereford+and+South+Herefordshire+MP+backs+Jacob+Rees-Mogg&sectionIs=news&searchyear=2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=2018-05-23 |title=Theresa May not an 'authentic Brexiteer' and could 'destabilise' Conservatives 'like never before' – MP |work=[[Sky_News|Sky News]] |url=https://news.sky.com/story/theresa-may-not-an-authentic-brexiteer-and-could-destabilise-conservatives-like-never-before-mp-11382608}}</ref>。前[[英國獨立黨|英國獨立黨]]黨魁和後來的[[英國脫歐黨|英國脫歐黨]]黨魁[[奈杰尔·法拉奇|奈杰尔·法拉奇]]都公開支持里斯-莫格參選<ref>{{Cite news |date=2017-10-04 |title=Nigel Farage Says Jacob Rees-Mogg Is The "Right Guy" To Be Next Tory Leader |work=[[LBC|LBC]] |url=https://www.lbc.co.uk/radio/presenters/nigel-farage/nigel-farage-says-jacob-rees-mogg-is-the-right-guy/}}</ref>。

2018年1月，他當選為保守黨內的疑歐派[[議會黨團|議會黨團]]{{le|欧洲研究小组|European Research Group}}主席<ref>{{Cite news |last=Swinford |first=Steven |date=2018-01-16 |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg to lead Eurosceptic Tory MPs and 'hold Government to account' over Brexit |work=[[The_Daily_Telegraph|The Daily Telegraph]] |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/politics/2018/01/16/exclusive-jacob-rees-mogg-lead-tory-eurosceptic-mps-hold-government/ |access-date=2018-01-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180118154516/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/politics/2018/01/16/exclusive-jacob-rees-mogg-lead-tory-eurosceptic-mps-hold-government/ |archive-date=2018-01-18}}</ref>。《[[獨立報|獨立報]]》的報道指出，這個身份令他能隨時有約50名保守黨國會議員的支持，足夠發動黨魁選舉<ref>{{Cite news |date=2018-02-03 |title=Don't underestimate Jacob Rees-Mogg – he is the Corbyn of the Conservative Party |work=The Independent |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/voices/jacob-reesmogg-protest-university-bristol-jeremy-corbyn-favourite-bookies-a8192781.html |access-date=2018-02-05}}</ref>。自此，里斯-莫格直接抨擊文翠珊和財相[[夏文達|夏文達]]的領導能力，令外界盛傳他正密謀策劃競逐黨魁，但他一直重申沒這樣的打算<ref>{{Cite news |date=2018-02-05 |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg attacks Theresa May and Philip Hammond as leadership speculation mounts |work=The Independent |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/jacob-rees-mogg-attacks-theresa-may-and-philip-hammond-leadership-a8196076.html |access-date=2018-02-06}}</ref>。同年2月，他在[[西英格蘭大學|西英格蘭大學]]發表演說時，有左翼示威者指罵他是一個種族主義者和偏執狂，最後演說被中斷，而該批示威者與里斯-莫格的支持者爆發暴力衝突<ref name="disruption">{{Cite news |last=Chloe Chaplain |date=2018-02-03 |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg caught up in scuffle at university politics event |work=Evening Standard |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/politics/jacob-reesmogg-caught-up-in-scuffle-at-university-politics-event-a3756981.html |access-date=2018-02-06}}</ref>。

里斯-莫格贊成他喜歡叫作「徹底脫歐」（{{lang|en|clean Brexit}}）的「硬脫歐」，他一直高調批評政府處理{{le|英國脫歐談判|Brexit negotiations}}的手法，特別是他稱爲「沒有成員國投票權地留在歐盟」、文翠珊所主導的「[[契克斯計劃|契克斯計劃]]」：
{{quote|首相（文翠珊）需要好好聽自己說過什麼、作過什麼許諾、還有上屆大選對選民的保證，再看看它們是否與契克斯計劃一致，我個人認為並不符合。如果她繼續堅持契克斯計劃，她會發現她在下議院中面臨一批反對票……當然，疑歐派在國會並不能在所有議題上構成大多數，但就契克斯計劃來說，我們無可避免地總會能在某些議題可以，而這樣會令政府的立法非常困難。<ref name="Whe19Aug2018">{{Cite news |last=Wheeler |first=Caroline |date=2018-08-19 |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg interview: boys, boys, let me sort Brexit first, then we can play cricket |work=The Sunday Times |url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/jacob-rees-mogg-interview-boys-boys-let-me-sort-brexit-first-then-we-can-play-cricket-987n9bbsd |access-date=2018-08-25}}</ref>}}

作為讓步，他亦會贊成「加拿大+」的協議，這方案可以讓英國與歐盟之間的貿易免關稅，但英國不需要留在歐盟的[[共同市場|共同市場]]或[[關稅同盟|關稅同盟]]內<ref name="Whe19Aug2018" />。

