里斯-莫格的政治觀點被形容為{{le|至高托利派|High Tory}}<ref>{{Cite web |date=2017-09-08 |title=The Great Brexit Shambles |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/09/08/opinion/jeremy-corbyn-theresa-may-brexit.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170909062628/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/09/08/opinion/jeremy-corbyn-theresa-may-brexit.html |archive-date=2017-09-09 |website=[[New_York_Times|New York Times]]}}</ref>、[[反动|反動主義]]<ref>{{Cite web |date=2017-08-12 |title=Artful Rees-Mogg is anything but a joke |url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/artful-rees-mogg-is-anything-but-a-joke-hhhvctlk3?shareToken=19010eb7baa202697539a2c486a70b9d |website=The Times}}</ref>、[[古典保守主义|傳統保守主義]]<ref>{{Cite web |date=2017-07-04 |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg and Nicky Morgan in Tory battle for top Westminster post |url=https://inews.co.uk/essentials/news/politics/jacob-rees-mogg-nicky-morgan-tory-battle-top-westminster-post/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170802005911/https://inews.co.uk/essentials/news/politics/jacob-rees-mogg-nicky-morgan-tory-battle-top-westminster-post/ |archive-date=2017-08-02 |website=[[i_(newspaper)|i News]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2017-07-22 |title=Tory members turn to David Davis in battle to succeed Theresa May |url=https://amp.theguardian.com/politics/2017/jul/22/david-davis-theresa-may-conservative-leadership |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170801234143/https://amp.theguardian.com/politics/2017/jul/22/david-davis-theresa-may-conservative-leadership |archive-date=2017-08-01 |website=[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]}}</ref>、{{le|英國民族主義|British nationalism|民族主義}}<ref>{{Cite web |last=Collins |first=Philip |date=2017-09-14 |title=Britain's new Gaullists |url=https://www.prospectmagazine.co.uk/magazine/britains-new-gaullists |website=[[Prospect_(magazine)|Prospect]]}}</ref>、[[社会保守主义|社会保守主义]]<ref>{{Cite news |date=2017-08-14 |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg fails to rule out a future bid to be next Conservative Party leader |work=[[Business_Insider|Business Insider]] |url=http://uk.businessinsider.com/jacob-rees-mogg-fails-to-rule-out-a-future-bid-to-be-next-conservative-party-leader-2017-8?r=US&IR=T |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170909190112/http://uk.businessinsider.com/jacob-rees-mogg-fails-to-rule-out-a-future-bid-to-be-next-conservative-party-leader-2017-8?r=US&IR=T |archive-date=2017-09-09}}</ref>，以及[[右翼民粹主義|右翼民粹主義]]<ref>{{Cite web |date=2017-07-14 |title=Populism's Latest Twist: An Aristocrat Could Be Britain's Prime Minister |url=http://observer.com/2017/07/jacob-rees-mogg-following-prime-minister/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170812214023/http://observer.com/2017/07/jacob-rees-mogg-following-prime-minister/ |archive-date=2017-08-12 |website=[[New_York_Observer|New York Observer]]}}</ref>，不過他不承認最後一項，強調他主張「受歡迎的政策，但不是民粹主義的政策」<ref>{{Cite news |date=2018-07-10 |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg: What I'd do as UK Home Secretary |work=The Spectator |url=https://spectator.us/2018/07/jacob-rees-mogg-what-id-do-as-uk-home-secretary/}}</ref>。 

里斯-莫格也是一個忠實的[[君主主義|君主主義者]]<ref name="oscar2">{{Cite news |date=2014-03-28 |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg on Downton Abbey, the Ukraine crisis, and taking famous women to a desert island |work=Chat Politics |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nh0Ewjyu6cE |access-date=2014-03-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140509150455/http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nh0Ewjyu6cE |archive-date=2014-05-09}}</ref>，亦是{{le|基石派|Cornerstone Group}}的成員<ref>{{Cite news |title=Who we are |publisher=Cornerstone Group |url=http://cornerstonegroup.wordpress.com/about/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070514042014/http://cornerstonegroup.wordpress.com/about/ |archive-date=2007-05-14}}</ref>。

=== 反對成為歐盟成員國 ===
里斯-莫格是[[英國去留歐盟公投|脫歐公投]]中脫歐運動的領軍人物，時常直言不諱的反對[[欧洲联盟|欧洲联盟]]<ref>{{Cite web |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg |url=http://www.parliament.uk/biographies/commons/mr-jacob-rees-mogg/4099 |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150709153604/http://www.parliament.uk/biographies/commons/mr-jacob-rees-mogg/4099 |archive-date=2015-07-09 |access-date=2012-10-14 |publisher=UK Parliament}}</ref>，他曾出席於不少訪問在這議題上辯論。有一次在[[牛津大學辯論社|牛津大學辯論社]]發言時，他形容歐盟為對英國民主以及國會主權的威脅，並以幾個國家反對[[欧盟宪法|欧盟宪法]]但最後卻透過[[里斯本条约|里斯本条约]]實施為例。<ref>{{Cite news |last=Waterfield |first=Bruno |date=2008-06-26 |title=EU Constitution author says referendums can be ignored |work=[[The_Daily_Telegraph|The Telegraph]] |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/2200026/EU-Constitution-author-says-referendums-can-be-ignored.html |dead-url=no |access-date=2017-09-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170907165603/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/2200026/EU-Constitution-author-says-referendums-can-be-ignored.html |archive-date=2017-09-07}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2016-06-28 |title=When France 'ignored' the result of an EU referendum |url=https://www.thelocal.fr/20160628/brexit-rethink-a-look-at-frances-2005-eu-referendum |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170907170158/https://www.thelocal.fr/20160628/brexit-rethink-a-look-at-frances-2005-eu-referendum |archive-date=2017-09-07 |access-date=2017-09-07 |website=[[The_Local|The Local]]}}</ref>他還讚揚[[民主统一党_(北爱尔兰)|民主統一黨]]摧毀了當時政府和歐盟的協定，「拯救了」英國脫歐。<ref>{{Cite news |date=2017-12-05 |title=As it happened: Govt wants UK-wide partial alignment |work=[[Sky_News|Sky News]] |url=https://news.sky.com/story/live-pm-fights-to-save-brexit-deal-11157154}}</ref>另外，他曾經在一次與[[德國另類選擇|德國另類選擇黨]]的代表會面後，批評該黨不夠疑歐，說「德國的疑歐派和英國的疑歐派相比，就像牛奶和白蘭地酒」。<ref>{{Cite web |date=2017-09-05 |title=An alternative Germany could well do without |url=https://capx.co/how-germanys-afd-lost-sight-of-its-liberal-roots/ |website=[[CapX|CapX]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2014-10-14 |title=The Mogg – a 'pale ale Nigel Farage' – in Germany |url=https://www.channel4.com/news/jacob-rees-mogg-germany-oktoberfest-eu-ukip-farage |website=[[Channel_4_News|Channel 4 News]]}}</ref>

=== 教育 ===
里斯-莫格與保守黨在教育上180度改變相反，他支持{{le|資助學校 (英國)|Academy (English school)|資助學校}}形式的教育，因為這樣可以給予學校更大決策自由度，不用再受制於地區教育部門和減低官僚主義。<ref>{{Cite web |date=2016-05-03 |title=Academisation |url=http://www.jacobreesmogg.com/academisation/ |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170907165531/http://www.jacobreesmogg.com/academisation/ |archive-date=2017-09-07 |access-date=2017-09-07 |website=jacobreesmogg.com}}</ref>在2005年為一些保守黨候選人站台時，他說取消就讀牛津大學或劍橋大學的候選人資格是不智的決定，還說國家由「盆栽植物」治理不會是最好。這被視為對沒上「牛劍」或[[公学|公学]]的人的攻擊，不少英國傳媒指責他[[精英主义|精英主义]]和勢利。<ref>{{Cite news |date=2011-07-07 |title=Somerset MP fails in speech bid |work=BBC News |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-somerset-14042106 |access-date=2018-04-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title='Toff' shrugs off class jibes in Somerset battle |work=Channel 4 News |url=http://www.channel4.com/news/articles/vote_2010/ampapostoffampapos+shrugs+off+class+jibes+in+somerset+battle/3620612.html |access-date=2018-04-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=2006-10-04 |title=State school pupils are 'potted plants', says Tory |work=The Independent |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/state-school-pupils-are-potted-plants-says-tory-418767.html |access-date=2018-02-06}}</ref>

=== 環境及氣候變化 ===
里斯-莫格曾在一些公共檔案<ref name=":4">{{Cite web |last=Rees-Mogg |first=Jacob |date=2012-05-10 |title=IS DISRAELI RIGHT: 'A SOUND CONSERVATIVE GOVERNMENT... TORY MEN AND WHIG MEASURES'? |url=https://brexitcentral.com/read-full-text-jacob-rees-mogg-brexit-speech/ |access-date=2019-07-28 |website=Centre for Policy Studies}}</ref><ref name="Ashcroft2019">Quoted in {{Cite book |last=Ashcroft |first=Michael |url=https://books.google.com.hk/books/about/Jacob_s_Ladder.html?id=BuidDwAAQBAJ&redir_esc=y |title=Jacob's Ladder: The Unauthorised Biography of Jacob Rees-Mogg |date=2019-09-10 |publisher=Biteback Publishing |isbn=978-1-78590-531-5 |page=157 |author-link=Michael Ashcroft}}</ref><ref name=":5">{{Cite web |last=Timsbury Environment Group |date=2012-10-01 |title=Carbon emissions and climate change: Report of a meeting with the Hon. Jacob Rees-Mogg |url=http://www.timsbury.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/RM-summary-for-website-version2.pdf |access-date=2019-08-15 |website=Timsbury our Community Website}}</ref>、文章<ref name=":6">{{Cite web |last=Rees-Mogg |first=Jacob |date=2013-10-23 |title=Climate change alarmism caused our high energy prices |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/politics/conservative/10398635/Climate-change-alarmism-caused-our-high-energy-prices.html |access-date=2019-08-15 |website=The Telegraph}}</ref><ref name=":7">{{Cite web |last=Rees-Mogg |first=Jacob |date=2012-01-30 |title=Full letter from MPs to David Cameron on wind power subsidies |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/earth/energy/windpower/9061554/Full-letter-from-MPs-to-David-Cameron-on-wind-power-subsidies.html |access-date=2019-08-15 |website=The Telegraph}}</ref>、訪問中<ref name="oscar2" /><ref name=":8">{{Cite web |last=Delingpole |first=James |date=2017-03-02 |title=Delingpole interviews Jacob Rees-Mogg |url=https://delingpoleworld.com/jacob-rees-mogg/ |access-date=2019-08-15 |website=Delingpole World}}</ref>，發表他對環境及氣候變化上與經濟方面掛鈎的觀點，認為保護環境的目標應該建基在經濟目的之上，而不是一種所謂「綠色的正統觀念」。<ref name=":4" />

他覺得價格低廉的能源在新興市場與競爭時尤其重要，並提倡繼續使用化石燃料。<ref name=":6" />

=== 經濟及勞工政策 ===
雖然里斯-莫格主要贊成[[自由市場|自由市場]]的經濟觀點，但是他因為受[[經濟自由主義|經濟自由主義者]][[罗伯特·皮尔|罗伯特·皮尔]]和[[贸易保护主义|貿易保護主義者]][[本傑明·迪斯雷利|本傑明·迪斯雷利]]的影響，亦同時認可一定程度的政府干預，相信改善人民的生活需要「政府使用一些既有的權力」。<ref>{{Cite news |date=2018-03-09 |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg: Tory Maoist |work=[[Politico|Politico]] |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/jacob-rees-mogg-maoist/}}</ref>

=== 外交關係 ===
里斯-莫格對英國捲入[[叙利亚内战|叙利亚内战]]的看法混雜<ref>{{Cite news |last=Rees-Mogg |first=Jacob |date=2013-06-18 |title=War in Syria: what would Thomas Aquinas do? |work=[[The_Daily_Telegraph|The Daily Telegraph]] |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/politics/10127537/War-in-Syria-what-would-Thomas-Aquinas-do.html |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170911065036/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/politics/10127537/War-in-Syria-what-would-Thomas-Aquinas-do.html |archive-date=2017-09-11}}</ref>，曾譴責武裝敘利亞叛軍，但其後在2013年亦曾投票支持針對[[巴沙尔·阿萨德|巴沙尔·阿萨德]]政權的英軍軍事行動<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2013-08-29/division/13082928001474/SyriaAndTheUseOfChemicalWeapons?outputType=Names|title=Division 70: held on Thursday 29 August 2013|website=[[英国议会|英国议会]]|date=2013-08-29|language=en}}</ref>。2015年10月，他形容「削弱阿薩德的後果就是恐怖主義抬頭和大規模的人口流動」。<ref>{{Cite web |date=2015-09-30 |title=October 2015 |url=http://www.mnrjournal.co.uk/article.cfm?id=4&classIS=column&headline=October%202015 |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170909232831/http://www.mnrjournal.co.uk/article.cfm?id=4&classIS=column&headline=October%202015 |archive-date=2017-09-09 |website=[[Midsomer_Norton,_Radstock_&_District_Journal|Midsomer Norton, Radstock & District Journal]]}}</ref>

他同時亦分別在2014年和2015年就對[[伊斯兰国|伊斯兰国]]及敘利亞的軍事行動投贊成票<ref>{{Cite news |date=2014-09-27 |title=How your MP voted on Iraq strikes |work=[[BBC|BBC]] |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-29386646}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=2015-12-03 |title=Syria strikes: Find out how your MP voted |work=[[BBC|BBC]] |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-34987921}}</ref>。

他形容[[外援|對國外的援助]]是一種"非常浪費政府支出的方式"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/conservative-leader-next-pm-foreign-aid-budget-political-football-theresa-may-a8877741.html|title=Foreign aid budget under threat with looming Tory leadership contest, warns Labour frontbencher|date=2019-04-20|website=The Independent}}</ref>，並支持《[[每日快報|每日快報]]》減低英國國外援助預算的行動<ref>{{Cite news |date=2018-02-08 |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg denies he is 'measuring the curtains' as he unexpectedly arrives at No 10 |work=[[i_(newspaper)|iNews]] |url=https://inews.co.uk/news/politics/jacob-rees-mogg-denies-measuring-curtains-unexpectedly-arrives-no-10/}}</ref>。

=== 移民 ===
里斯-莫格曾投票支持一個更嚴厲的庇護系統和多加入境檢查的移民政策，以減低淨移民的數量<ref>{{Cite web |date=2015-05-22 |title=Immigration |url=http://www.jacobreesmogg.com/immigration/ |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170907212620/http://www.jacobreesmogg.com/immigration/ |archive-date=2017-09-07 |access-date=2017-09-07 |website=jacobreesmogg.com}}</ref>。據[[奈杰尔·法拉奇|奈杰尔·法拉奇]]所述，里斯-莫格相信脫歐派「贏得公投」的關鍵是，一幅印有「失控點」連同一列列敘利亞難民進入歐洲的海報<ref>{{Cite news |date=2017-12-08 |title=Nigel Farage: the arsonist in exile |work=[[New_Statesman|New Statesman]] |url=https://www.newstatesman.com/politics/uk/2017/12/nigel-farage-arsonist-exile}}</ref>。里斯-莫格贊同停止{{le|歐盟勞動人口自由流動|Freedom of movement for workers in the European Union|人口自由流動}}前往英國，但他希望非英國公民而居住在英國的[[欧盟公民|欧盟公民]]得以「大致上享有與英國公民同等的權利，不較為好亦不較為差」，他們的權利亦不應有追溯性地被撤銷<ref>{{Cite news |last=Cowburn |first=Ashley |date=2018-08-20 |title=EU migrants 'to get right to remain' in UK in event of no-deal Brexit |work=The Independent |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/brexit-latest-eu-migrants-right-remain-uk-no-deal-a8498746.html |access-date=2018-09-01}}</ref>。

2018年5月，他批評[[文翠珊|文翠珊]]目標減少移民至每年10萬個為太低，形容這目標數字只是「隨口說出」，英國脫歐不應是如此「升起吊橋」而是能對移民有更多的控制，他亦提議學生簽證可不被計算在官方移民數字中<ref>{{Cite news |date=2018-05-22 |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg slams Theresa May's 'idiotic' 100,000 immigration target |work=PoliticsHome |url=https://www.politicshome.com/news/uk/home-affairs/immigration/news/95388/jacob-rees-mogg-slams-theresa-mays-%E2%80%98idiotic%E2%80%99-100000}}</ref>。

=== 社會議題 ===
就[[同性婚姻|同性婚姻]]，里斯-莫格曾表示反對，也並不為其合法化而感到自豪，而且認為這會疏遠保守黨的傳統支持者<ref>{{Cite news |title=Owen Jones talks to Jacob Rees-Mogg: 'I'm not in favour of this new-age drippiness' |work=The Guardian |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2015/dec/02/owen-jones-jacob-rees-mogg-no-easy-answers-syria |dead-url=no |access-date=2016-04-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160416002109/http://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2015/dec/02/owen-jones-jacob-rees-mogg-no-easy-answers-syria |archive-date=2016-04-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last1=Duffy |first1=Nick |last2=McCormick |first2=Joseph Patrick |date=2015-01-31 |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg: The PM is 'rubbing in gay marriage' |work=Pink News |url=https://www.pinknews.co.uk/2015/01/31/exclusive-jacob-rees-mogg-attacks-pm-for-rubbing-it-in-that-same-sex-marriage-passed/ |dead-url=no |access-date=2015-05-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150504163700/http://www.pinknews.co.uk/2015/01/31/exclusive-jacob-rees-mogg-attacks-pm-for-rubbing-it-in-that-same-sex-marriage-passed/ |archive-date=2015-05-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Merrick |first=Jane |date=2015-02-01 |title=MP Jacob Rees-Mogg tells Tory activists he is 'not proud' of gay marriage law |work=The Independent |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/mp-jacob-reesmogg-tells-tory-activists-he-is-not-proud-of-gay-marriage-law-10016072.html |dead-url=no |access-date=2015-05-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150507025243/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/mp-jacob-reesmogg-tells-tory-activists-he-is-not-proud-of-gay-marriage-law-10016072.html |archive-date=2015-05-07}}</ref>。2013年，他說在同性婚姻的議題上，他「所遵循的黨鞭指令是來自羅馬天主教會，而不是（保守黨）黨鞭辦公室」<ref>{{Cite news |last=Lusher |first=Adam |date=2017-08-13 |title=Saviour of the Tory party or 'reactionary poison'? Will Jacob Rees-Mogg run for Tory leader, and what would he do as PM? |work=Independent |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/jacob-rees-mogg-moggmentum-run-for-tory-leader-leadership-election-contest-conservative-party-a7891196.html |dead-url=no |access-date=2017-09-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170909004817/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/jacob-rees-mogg-moggmentum-run-for-tory-leader-leadership-election-contest-conservative-party-a7891196.html |archive-date=2017-09-09}}</ref>。他其後解釋「婚姻是[[聖禮|聖禮]]的一種，而聖禮該怎樣執行應該是教會的決定，不是國會」<ref name="Sawer">{{Cite news |last=Sawer |first=Patrick |date=2017-09-09 |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg: 'I oppose same-sex marriage, but I'd go to a gay wedding' |work=[[The_Daily_Telegraph|The Telegraph]] |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/09/09/jacob-rees-mogg-oppose-same-sex-marriage-go-gay-wedding/ |dead-url=no |access-date=2017-09-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170909114602/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/09/09/jacob-rees-mogg-oppose-same-sex-marriage-go-gay-wedding/ |archive-date=2017-09-09}}</ref>。

== 個人生活 ==
里斯-莫格是{{le|聖潘克拉斯市長列表|List of mayors of St Pancras|聖潘克拉斯自治市前市長}}托馬斯·理查德·莫里斯（{{lang|en|Thomas Richard Morris}}）的外孫，和英國奧運跨欄代表選手{{le|第七代從男爵勞倫斯·克拉克爵士|Sir Lawrence Clarke, 7th Baronet|勞倫斯·克拉克爵士}}的姨丈<ref>{{Cite news |last=Hart |first=Simon |date=2010-09-28 |title=Charles Lawrence Somerset Clarke eyes next hurdle |work=The Daily Telegraph |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/othersports/commonwealthgames/8028194/Commonwealth-Games-2010-Charles-Lawrence-Somerset-Clarke-eyes-next-hurdle.html |access-date=2020-04-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150226030112/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/othersports/commonwealthgames/8028194/Commonwealth-Games-2010-Charles-Lawrence-Somerset-Clarke-eyes-next-hurdle.html |archive-date=2015-02-26}}</ref>。

2006年，里斯-莫格與貿易雜誌專欄作家海倫娜·安妮·比阿特麗克斯·溫特沃斯·菲茨威廉·德切爾（{{lang|en|Helena Anne Beatrix Wentworth Fitzwilliam de Chair}}）訂婚，她是{{le|薩默塞特·德切爾|Somerset de Chair}}和其第四任妻子{{le|朱麗葉·塔德格爾女勳爵|Lady Juliet Tadgell}}的獨生女，二人兒時已相識。里斯-莫格得到德切爾母親的祝福才開始約會，交往了一年便已訂婚。<ref>{{Cite news |date=2010-03-09 |title=The Innocent smoothies of politics are still the party of the rich |work=The Guardian |url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2010/mar/09/smoothies-party-rich-tories-brand |access-date=2018-02-05}}</ref>二人於2007年在[[坎特伯雷座堂|坎特伯雷座堂]]結成夫婦，他們的{{le|保祿六世彌撒|Mass of Paul VI|後梵二<!--梵蒂岡第二屆大公會議-->彌撒}}儀式是以[[拉丁文|拉丁文]]舉行<ref>{{Cite web |date=2018-03-27 |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg: I try to say the rosary every day |url=https://catholicherald.co.uk/news/2018/03/27/jacob-rees-mogg-i-try-to-say-the-rosary-every-day/ |access-date=2019-07-24 |website=Catholic Herald}}</ref>。 

[[File:Gournay_Court.jpg|thumb]]
2006年，里斯-莫格跟其妻子購買了{{le|古爾奈庭院|Gournay Court}}，是一幢座落於{{le|西哈普特里|West Harptree}}的[[登錄建築|二級登錄建築]]，亦是里斯-莫格的大姨母以志願護士、護士長身份在[[第一次世界大战|第一次世界大战]]服務的前[[国际红十字与红新月运动|紅十字]]醫院，二人在這裡養育六名子女<ref>{{NHLE|desc=Gourney Court|num=1129581|accessdate=2018-02-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2014-05-28 |title=World War One At Home – Gournay Court |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p01xtjjw |access-date=2018-02-06 |website=BBC One}}</ref><ref name="BBC 5 July 2017">{{Cite web |date=2017-07-05 |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg announces baby Sixtus |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-40506109 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170705104711/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-40506109 |archive-date=2017-07-05 |access-date=2017-07-05 |website=[[BBC_News_Online|BBC News Online]] |publisher=BBC}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2014-05-28 |title=Gournay Court, Somerset: Remembering a Great Aunt |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p01xtjjw |access-date=2017-01-31 |publisher=BBC}}</ref>。

2017年7月，里斯-莫格曾說：「我完全不會假裝我是一個現代男性，從來都不會」，並同時說自己沒有換過[[尿片|尿布]]，稱：「我不覺得我們的保姆會認可，因為我肯定她會認為我不能妥當地做好」<ref name=":1" />。維羅妮卡·克魯克（Veronica Crook）自1965年服務里斯-莫格的家族，從他4歲起便是他的保姆，現在亦是他六名孩子的保姆<ref>{{Cite news |last=Horton |first=Helena |date=2017-08-15 |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg puts nanny front and centre in family photograph |work=The Telegraph |publisher=telegraph.co.uk |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/08/15/jacob-rees-mogg-puts-nanny-front-centre-family-photograph/ |access-date=2019-03-26}}</ref>。2017年7月，工黨國會議員[[夏雅雯|夏雅雯]]認為「不換尿布的男性都是遊手好閒的爸爸，包括雅各·里斯-莫格」<ref name="Asthana">{{Cite news |last=Asthana |first=Anushka |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg is a 'deadbeat dad', says Harriet Harman |work=The Guardian |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/sep/09/jacob-rees-mogg-is-a-deadbeat-dad-says-harriet-harman |access-date=2017-09-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170909055155/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/sep/09/jacob-rees-mogg-is-a-deadbeat-dad-says-harriet-harman |archive-date=2017-09-09}}</ref>。

作為{{le|國會跨黨派小組|All-party parliamentary group|國會跨黨派歷史車輛小組}}成員，里斯-莫格對歷史車輛頗有興趣。23歲的時候，他買了一輛板球運動員{{le|古比·艾倫|Gubby Allen}}先前擁有過的{{le|賓利T系列|Bentley T-series|1968年的賓利T系列}}。2005年，他為他的收藏系列添了一輛{{le|賓利3.5升|Bentley 3.5 Litre|1936的賓利3.5升}}和一輛作日常代步的[[凌志|凌志]]<ref>{{Cite news |last=Coates |first=Ashley |date=2016-10-06 |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg on his first Alfa, Bentleys and the joys of classic motoring |work=[[Evening_Standard|Evening Standard]] |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/lifestyle/motors/jacob-reesmogg-on-his-first-alfa-bentleys-and-the-joys-of-classic-cars-a3352151.html |access-date=2017-09-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170906225219/https://www.standard.co.uk/lifestyle/motors/jacob-reesmogg-on-his-first-alfa-bentleys-and-the-joys-of-classic-cars-a3352151.html |archive-date=2017-09-06}}</ref>。里斯-莫格亦愛好板球，青年時期開始已經是{{le|森麻實郡板球俱樂部|Somerset County Cricket Club}}的支持者<ref>{{Cite web |title=Meet Jacob |url=http://www.jacobreesmogg.com/about/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161202165629/http://www.jacobreesmogg.com/about/ |archive-date=2016-12-02 |access-date=2017-09-17 |website=www.jacobreesmogg.com}}</ref>。

2018年5月，他購買了在[[西敏寺|西敏寺]]後方、位於考利街、價值5百萬英鎊的物業<ref>{{Cite news |last=Kentish |first=Benjamin |date=2018-05-27 |title=Jacob Rees-Mogg takes aim at Theresa May over Brexit and Northern Ireland border |work=The Independent |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/brexit-latest-jacob-rees-theresa-may-error-northern-ireland-border-customs-union-a8371431.html |access-date=2018-06-02}}</ref>。

